I would like to see Tim Burton direct a movie by Neil Gaimon!

Yes, I am a fan girl...


The first step is admitting it, right?

My dream movie: Screen Play: by Neil Gaimon Staring: Gary Oldman, Johnny Depp, and Cate Blanchett I have no idea what this movie would be about. But I think it could be amazing, especially if I could come up with someone to direct it. I thought for a moment about Yimou Zhang, but I've only seen 2 of his movies (House of Flying Daggers and Hero) and I'm worried that he only knows how to direct one kind of movie. I thought both of those movies were really well done, and visually stunning. I also thought about Sam Raimi and also about Peter Jackson, but here again, I've only seen one type of movie that they have each done (I'm not taking Evil Dead and Army of Darkness into consideration for the films he's directed). But once I've found a director, I'll have the makings for a fabulous movie! *goes off searching through the I.M.D.B. looking for a good director*

Log of Captin Jasmine the Just. On this Twenty-Seventh day of September in the Year of Our Lord two thousand and five I have had a fortunate encounter with one Egore Pebody. He is an accomplished stone carver and earns his way making tomb stones. Just knowing of him has reminded me of a pending need. In the unfortunate event that I am unable to capture the knave Capt. Mad Pirate Em. and she flees from justice into the arms of death, I should, being a responsible Privateer, have a tomb stone ready to mark her grave. For though she would surly be taken to a watery grave, I am a Christian captian and I shall make a grave for her, though it be empty that it may be a reminder to all who dare cross paths with my well kept ship. The good mister Pebody has even furnished me a sketch of the prospective grave marker so that I may have a its pleasant image to keep me company in my cabin.

 in the unfortunate event that she would need one.

As I am a faithful servant of our good King William I begin this log as he has commanded me in his Letter of Mark and Reprisal on this twenty-second of September in the Year of our Lord two thousand and five. We have had an unidentified ship in our sites for some months now. And our suspicions of this ship were many. They were confirmed on twentieth September in the Year of our Lord two thousand and five. On that day the aforementioned ship ran up its colors and Capt. Mad Pirate Em. declared herself the villain she is before God and Heritage Hill. The presence of the other renegades has been confirmed as well. Having been recently refitted with sufficient battery and artillery and as our ship is fresh cleaned and painted, I feel confident that God and Country will bless the days ahead and we shall emerge victorious. I stand ready at the prow, having been freshly bathed and uniforms newly starched. My crew is in proper order and ready to face the coming days with courage and resolve. My First Mate, Kyle of Monteith, has reviewed the battle plans and confirms my tactics. Mia the Muscle and Yumi the Cunning, my brave crew, have received their orders and are poised for the coming struggle. With a steady (white gloved) hand do I engage in battle. With a heart filled by Righteousness do I confront these villains. God Save the King!

LJ Interests meme results

  1. art deco:
    My favorite art movement and historic time period. I love the clean, classic lines.
  2. beading:
    Something useful to do with my hands! Much more productive than doodling.
  3. catholicism:
    As in Recovering...
  4. costuming:
    The possibilities! The color! The Sewing! Creativity in a pattern envelope. I'll never get over playing dress up!
  5. house plants:
    All the fun of green growing things without the bugs and the weather.
  6. knitting:
    Something useful to do with my hands! Much more productive than doodling.
  7. manga:
    Little bits of romance and drama that I can read in an hour. And ofcourse the PRETTY pictures are important too.
  8. neopets:
    I get something other than a high score when I play the games. Granted the "something" is points that I can put toward feeding and playing with my virtual pet...but it's "something" and that's all that matters.
  9. reading:
    So many possibilities! So many characters! And they can all be pretty and effeminate in my head!
  10. scotch:
    Yuuummm...and cigars...and Miles Davis on the CD player. The perfect end to a long day.

As many of you know, Kyle and I got a new cat about 10 days ago. Her name is Yumi and she is a Siamese with calico coloring. She is so pretty. She is only 7 mths old and she is the most laid back (almost lazy really) kitten I have ever met. But she is so affectionate and cuddly. She starts purring as soon as you pick her up and can not get enough attention. Our other cat, Mia is almost the opposit. She is such a tom-boy of a cat. She loves to play and will only stand to be cuddled for just so long before she has be moving again. The two cats are getting along pretty well. They play together and cuddle together when we are not looking (occasionally we catch them at it). Mia is 10 months old and Yumi is already the same size as her. But that doesn't stop Mia from being the Alpha cat.
